<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-178-062  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 178 062.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Healthcare  April 1989 v10 n4 p27(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lahey Clinic: implementing an order-entry and result-reportingsystem for cardiac testing using PCS-ADS. (Lahey Clinic MedicalCenter in Massachusetts) (IBM Patient Care System-ApplicationApplication Development System)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Turisco, Frances J.; McMackin, Ann P.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Burlington, MA's Lahey Clinic Medical Center used IBM's PatientCare System-Application Development System (PCS-ADS) to develop anonline patient order-entry and result-reporting system for cardiactesting in the Center's Electrocardiography (ECG) andEchocardiography (ECHO) Laboratories.andP;  A large and rapidlyexpanding work volume resulted in growing inefficiencies inrecording, reporting, and filing of results; billing; and, even,delay of surgery.andP;  The new system was specified, designed, andimplemented within one year with PCS-ADS.andP;  A real-time interfaceto the laboratories' MUSE (Marquette electrocardiography readingsystem) was implemented in one month.andP;  Benefits include improvedworkflow, testing to online results arrive in under five minutes,more accurate collection of charges and statistics and onlineavailability of and current and previous results.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Patient Care System-Application Development System (computerprogram) (usage).andO;Topic:     Lahey Clinic Medical CenterCase StudyHospital Information SystemsHospitalHealth CareCost Benefit Analysis.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>